decision_conditions:
Condition : 20 - Prior to the first use of the construction access as identified on the approved Site Logistics Plan, a Construction Logistics Plan (in report form) shall be submitted to and agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Heavy vehicles are to be routed to avoid travelling the residential areas near the site with no access through Lionel Road North. 
 
The Construction Logistics Plan (CLP) should include:
(i). Anticipated duration of construction period;
(ii). Junction modelling of the worst case inter-peak hour, which shall include a plan showing where the stop line will be located within the park (ample inter-green and green time will need to be included within the model to demonstrate that this arm can operate safely);
(iii). A programme of the anticipated duration of movements (in TfL format);
(iv). A proposed cap on hourly vehicle numbers;
(v). A series of measures to ensure that pedestrian safety is not compromised at the junction (e.g. banksman);
(vi). Closure of construction access and road to pedestrians;
(vii). Measures to ensure that the park arm phase is not called every traffic light cycle (e.g. loop to detect vehicles);
(viii). Details of how dust and dirt will be managed;
(ix). Measures to re-instate the access on completion of works;
(x). Using operators committed to best practice, demonstrated by membership of TfL's Freight Operator Recognition Scheme (FORS) or similar.

The use of this access throughout the construction period shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Localised traffic issues at the Pope's Lane / Lionel Road North junction should be monitored and the CLP amended to reflect any issues that might arise.
